\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {S1}{\ignorespaces Venus protein levels measured for two cases: addition of \textit  {P.~aeruginosa} GntR gene and in the absence of GntR gene. Linear DNA used were: mP70-Venus (7 nM), P70-GntR (0 or 10 nM). The \textit  {P.~aeruginosa} GntR variant does not bind to the \textit  {E.~coli} GntR operator, serving as a control for resource competition effects.}}{S-54}{}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:S1}{{S1}{S-54}{}{}{}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {S2}{\ignorespaces Pairwise projections of the six-dimensional Pareto front. Grey points represent the 41,280 archive solutions with total error $< 100$ (out of 73,747 total); blue points represent the $N = 78$ filtered ensemble members. \textbf  {A}: Venus mRNA SSE versus Venus protein SSE. \textbf  {B}: Venus protein SSE at 10 mM versus no-GntR control. \textbf  {C}: Venus protein SSE at 10 mM versus 0 mM (repressed). \textbf  {D}: Venus mRNA SSE versus GntR mRNA SSE. The filtered ensemble occupies the corner of the Pareto front where all objectives are simultaneously minimized.}}{S-55}{}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:pareto_fronts}{{S2}{S-55}{}{}{}}
\providecommand\NAT@force@numbers{}\NAT@force@numbers
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {S3}{\ignorespaces Marginal parameter distributions across the filtered ensemble ($N = 78$). Each panel shows the histogram for one of the 25 estimated parameters. Black vertical lines indicate the ensemble mean; red dashed lines indicate the parameter bounds (where visible within the axis range). Parameters with narrow, unimodal distributions (e.g., $K_{\text  {gluconate}}$, $n_{\text  {gluconate}}$, $\alpha _X$) are well-identified by the data, while parameters with broad distributions (e.g., $K_{\text  {Venus},\sigma _{70}}$, $\delta _{p,\text  {Venus}}$) or distributions piling against bounds (e.g., $\delta _{m,\text  {Venus}}$, $n_{\text  {Venus,GntR}}$) indicate structural identifiability limitations.}}{S-56}{}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:param_dist}{{S3}{S-56}{}{}{}}
